{"readme":"<h1 class=\"title\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://github.com/stackgl/glsl-look-at\">glsl-look-at</a><div class=\"contrib\"></div></h1>\n<p><a href=\"http://github.com/badges/stability-badges\"></a></p>\n<p>Generates a 3D lookAt matrix in GLSL.</p>\n<h2 id=\"usage\">Usage</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://nodei.co/npm/glsl-look-at/\"></a></p>\n<h3 id=\"mat3-lookat-vec3-origin-vec3-target-float-roll-\"><code>mat3 lookAt(vec3 origin, vec3 target, float roll)</code></h3>\n<p>Creates a <code>mat3</code> matrix you can use to transform coordinates\nto look towards a given point, where:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>origin</code> is the position of the camera.</li>\n<li><code>target</code> is the position to look towards.</li>\n<li><code>roll</code> is the roll rotation of the camera.</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-glsl\"><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span>#</span><span class=\"meta preprocessor keyword import define glsl\"><span>pragma&#xA0;glslify:</span></span><span class=\"entity name function glsl\"><span>&#xA0;lookAt&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"operator glsl\"><span>=&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"keyword operator glsl\"><span>require</span></span><span>(</span><span class=\"string quoted double\"><span>&apos;glsl-look-at&apos;</span></span><span>)</span><span>&#xA0;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"storage modifier glsl\"><span>uniform</span></span><span>&#xA0;</span><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>vec2</span></span><span>&#xA0;iResolution;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source glsl\"><span class=\"storage type glsl\"><span>void</span></span><span class=\"meta function c\"><span class=\"punctuation whitespace function leading c\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span><span class=\"entity name function c\"><span